Object.Field: IKM Sybase IQ Slowly Changing Dimension

Author: Sunopsis Version: 4.0 Last Update: DEC-2004
Description: - Integration Knowledge Module - Management of TYPE 2 Slowly Changing Dimensions on Sybase Adaptive Server IQ (12.4.3 or later). - Data can be controlled. Invalid data is isolated in the Error Table and can be recycled.
To use this Knowledge Module: When defining the Target Datastore, it is necessary to set the following parameters (from the "Slowly Changing Dimensions Behavior" list box, on the "Description" tab of each column concerned): - Surrogate Key: A single column identifying Records. This column must be defined as an Identity column on the Target Data Server and should be: - Mapped to 0 (zero), - Executed on Target - Natural Key: Column(s) representing the Natural Key of the Record. - Overwrite Column: List of updatable column(s) (i.e. those that can be updated after modification of the original data). - Insert Row: List of column(s) representing the Slowly Changing Attributes (i.e. those that require a Record insert after modification of the original data) - Current Record Flag: A single numeric column mapped to 0 or 1 and representing the Current Record Flag status of the Record. It is automatically updated by the Knowledge Module (1 : Current Record ; 0 : Past Records) - Start Timestamp: A single date (or timestamp) column indicating the beginning of a Record's availability. The value is the current date (or timestamp). - End Timestamp: A single date (or timestamp) column indicating the end of the Record's availability. The value is a default of "01 January 2400"
Restrictions: - You should use at least Sybase AS IQ 12.4.3 - When an Integration Interface using this Knowledge Module is used from a Package, then the option COMMIT should be set to YES for each Integration Interface composing the Package. - Make sure to map ALL target table columns flagged as: "Surrogate Key", "Natural Key", "Current Record Flag", "Start Timestamp" and "End Timestamp". Notice that mappings set for the "Current Record Flag", "Start Timestamp" and "End Timestamp" columns are not used. - As this Knowledge Module is dedicated to Datawarehouse Projects (where data should not be removed), when using it with a journalized Source Datastore, it is not possible to synchronize deletions. Therefore, data should be manually filtered to exclude any source delete events (add a filter on JRN_FLAG = 'I'). - The TRUNCATE option cannot work if the target table is referenced by another table (i.e. with a Foreign Key). - Deletes are committed regardless of the COMMIT option. - The FLOW_CONTROL and STATIC_CONTROL options call the Check Knowledge Module to isolate invalid data (if no CKM is set, an error occurs). Both options must be set to NO in the case when an Integration Interface populates a TEMPORARY target datastore. If the Table Primary Key is designated by the same column as the Surrogate Key, then: 1. On the "Diagram" tab of the Interface, uncheck the "Check Not Null" checkbox for the column representing the Primary Key. 2. On the "Control" tab of the Interface and in the "Constraint" panel, set the option value to NO for the Primary Key control. - Regardless to the COMMIT option, the COMMIT is always execued.
